  "description": "A field is a commutative [ring](./ring.md) in which every nonzero element has a multiplicative inverse. Equivalently, a field is a set with addition and multiplication such that both $(F, +, 0)$ and $(F setminus {0}, cdot, 1)$ are [abelian groups](../../../objects/groups/terms/abelian-group.md), and multiplication distributes over addition.",
